Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Sophia Johns

2023-03-12

My Meme

My meme is a funny cat meme about the realities of owning a cat. 

library(magick)
# women screaming meme
#background for text
women_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
            height = 500,
            color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me giving my cat constant love and attention",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Impact")
# image for meme
women_meme <- image_read("https://wompampsupport.azureedge.net/fetchimage?siteId=7575&v=2&jpgQuality=100&width=700&url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.kym-cdn.com%2Fphotos%2Fimages%2Fnewsfeed%2F001%2F505%2F717%2F49b.jpg") 

  
# cat meme
# background for text
cat_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
            height = 500,
            color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "My cat just waking up from her nap",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Impact")
# image for meme
cat_meme <- image_read("https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/549/cpsprodpb/1261C/production/_100729257_photojan0574306am.jpg") 

  
# appending the meme
  top_row <- image_append(c(women_text, cat_text)) 
  
  bottom_row <- image_append(c(women_meme, cat_meme)) 
  
  
 meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
    image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
    image_scale(800) %>%

# saving the meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My Animated GIF

My GIF is is an animation of different coloured shapes which I thought looked nice together and make an animation about colour and geometry which would be useful for children. 

library(magick)
# images
circle_image <- image_read("https://png.pngtree.com/png-clipart/20201208/original/pngtree-circle-clipart-bright-green-circle-png-image_5553157.jpg") 
  image_scale(500)
star_image <- image_read("https://www.gamefaces.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/B-99-P.png") 
  image_scale(500)
square_image <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/originals/eb/7b/27/eb7b27fb83a4bf2cd50184869b47d9aa.jpg") 
  image_scale(500)
triangle_image <- image_read("https://w7.pngwing.com/pngs/151/1018/png-transparent-yellow-triangle-triangle-yellow-pyramid-pattern-triangle-angle-orange-shape.png") 
  image_scale(500)
# creating each frame
frame1 <- circle_image %>%
  image_scale(200) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame2 <- star_image %>%
  image_scale(300) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame3 <- square_image %>%
  image_scale(400) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame4 <- triangle_image %>%
  image_scale(500)
image_extent("500x500")

# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# creating an animation
gif <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

# saving the gif
image_write(gif, "my_gif.gif")
